  "prompt": "How do I add question details digitally on Quora?",
  "response": "To add question details digitally on Quora, follow these steps:\n\n1. **Sign In**: Go to the Quora website or open the Quora app and sign in to your account. If you don\u2019t have an account, you\u2019ll need to create one.\n\n2. **Ask a Question**:\n   - On the Quora homepage, look for the \"Ask Question\" button, usually located at the top of the page.\n   - Click on it to open the question submission box.\n\n3. **Enter Your Question**: Type your question in the box that appears. Make sure it is clear and specific to attract relevant answers.\n\n4. **Add Details**:\n   - After typing your question, you can click on the \"Add Question Details\" link or option (if available) to provide additional context or background information about your question.\n   - Include any relevant information that may help others understand the question better, such as your specific interests, any constraints, or what type of answers you are looking for.\n\n5. **Choose Topics**: Quora allows you to add topics related to your question. This helps categorize your question and makes it easier for others interested in those topics to find it. Start typing in the topics box, and select from the suggestions that appear.\n\n6. **Review and Submit**: Once you\u2019ve added your question and any additional details, review everything to ensure clarity and completeness. Then, click the \"Submit\" button to post your question.\n\n7. **Engage with Answers**: After your question is posted, you can engage with the answers you receive by upvoting, commenting, or sharing your thoughts.\n\nRemember to abide by Quora's community guidelines when asking questions, and ensure that your question is appropriate for the platform.",
